ch event, so that would have to be assigned dynamically for each individual event, and probably arranged on the boards prior.<br><br>2)  To minimize the organizational nightmare this would cause for re-forming of guilds, guild officers would (as you said) need to be placed at numerous locations around the world.  It would probably be beneficial to identify the common raid locations (Hate, Fear, Kael, Kedge, wherever...) and have every guild place mule officers at those pre-designated places (SRo spires, Feerot portal, etc.).  However, the mule officers would have to be on multiple people's accounts, since you have to accomodate for the GL not being able to attend every event.  As long as the events SGA runs were set out with a good amount of time in advance, this should not be a problem.  <br><br>3)  What would be ideal would be for each guild to have an extra account for SGA purposes, and have a character on that account as an SGA officer.  Each active SGA player would have access to their guild's account, and that way it would not matter who is attending.  One person would log on the other account and pass out the memberships.  The problem with that would be lack of accountability, so it probably would not work.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Anyway Boofa, I applaud your active interest in improving the state of things, and I thank everyone who is making a strong effort to accomplish the vision of the SGA.<br><br>Dehglor Valorcry<br>50th season Paladin<br>Wings of the Chimera <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goishen>Goishen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/7/01 9:27:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.